<img src="/assets/graphics/peer_program.png" alt="">
			<h4>PAIR PROGRAMMING</h4>
			<p class="">
Building software together in pairs. Pair programming is an agile software development technique in which two programmers work together at one workstation. One, the driver, writes code while the other, the observer, pointer or navigator, reviews each line of code as it is typed in. The two programmers switch roles frequently.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="3u text-center">
<img src="/assets/graphics/design_stack.png" alt="">
			<h4>INTERACTIVE DESIGNING</h4>
			<p class="">
Fun and interactive design on the web using modern tools. HTML5, CSS3 and JavaScript are the newest stars of the web: the cornerstones of progressive enhancement, the easiest way to build web applications for desktop and mobile devices, and a brilliant foundation upon which we can add complex interaction and animation layers to the web. :)
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="3u text-center">
<img src="/assets/graphics/hardware.png" alt="">
			<h4>HARDWARE HACKING</h4>
			<p class="">
Coming up with innovative solutions using microcontrollers, hardware and computer circuit design. Nowadays it is easy to research, design, develop, and test new systems using fairly affordable microcontrollers, circuit boards, memory devices, networks, and routers, and other embedded sensors. These include the Arduino or Raspberry Pi. 
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="3u text-center">
<img src="/assets/graphics/video_camera.png" alt="">
			<h4>FILM DOCUMENTARY!</h4>
			<p class="">
The trip will be documented on a film. This will cover the Events, interviews and the travel experience. The film will be published by the end of the year to serve as a motivational and educational piece for more startups that may not get the same opportunity. There will also be plenty of blogs and photos.
			</p>
		</div>

